    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and grate <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-meatball-and-tomato-farfalle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>beef mince</strong>, <strong>grated onion</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>to a bowl</p><p>Mix thoroughly until fully combined (clean hands is the best way!), divide the beef mixture and shape into 3 <strong>meatballs</strong> per person</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-meatball-and-tomato-farfalle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned</p><p>Once the meatballs have browned, transfer them to a plate and set aside (reserve the pan!), these will finish cooking in the sauce later</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-meatball-and-tomato-farfalle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-meatball-and-tomato-farfalle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-meatball-and-tomato-farfalle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to soften, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>beef stock mix</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Return the <strong>browned meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato sauce & beef meatballs</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-meatball-and-tomato-farfalle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>farfalle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>farfalle</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-meatball-and-tomato-farfalle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>farfalle</strong> topped with the <strong>tomato sauce & beef meatballs</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
